<font color="#FF0000">CONTROL ONLY SOME THINGS</font><br>
<tt>Wed Sep 24  0:19:18 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Ed,<br><br>
A small thought.  If we control everything we lose our asperations <br>
dreams, and desires.  We don't need them, we are in control.  If <br>
control everything we lose our emotions, the intense ones of love, hate,<br>
are sacrificed to control fear.<br><br>
The secret of success is finding those things you have to control.  To control <br>
everything we lose a little of our humanity.  Those softer emtions of <br>
empathy, sympathy, and compassion are lost.  The very things we seek from others.  <br><br>
Trust and self confidence are also a form of control.  Self esteem gives us <br>
control over our self image.  I'm OK your OK.  Simple, but true.<br>
I propose we have many of the fears and instincts of young children who also lack <br>
control and understanding.  They find comfort in being able to <br>
totally trust someone.<br><br>
Control the right things and leave a little of yourself.  Those you <br>
trust and love will take care of the rest.  When we accept that premise <br>
we should be on our way to controlling fear.<br>

<p><code>--   (SW) </code><p>


